  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The late-time dynamics of massive spin-2 fields in flat and curved spacetimes are studied analytically. We find that the time evolutions of the massive fields are characterized by oscillatory power-law decaying tails at asymptotically late times. In a flat spacetime the decaying exponent depends on the multipole number and the parity of the mode. In the curved Schwarzschild black-hole spacetime the decaying exponent is found to be universal.</subfield>
    <subfield code="9">arXiv</subfield>
  </datafield>
