  <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
    <subfield code="o">24</subfield>
    <subfield code="m">Defining œÜ ‚â° œà1 + b ¬∑ œà2 + c ¬∑ œà3, one obtains from Eqs. (25)-(27) the wave equation: ( d2 dr2 + œâ2 - ¬µ2 )œÜ - l(l+1)+6-6b r2 {œà1 + -2l(l+1)+b[l(l+1)+4]+2c l(l+1)+6-6b œà2 + 2b[l(l+1)-2]+c[l(l+1)-2] l(l+1)+6-6b œà3} = 0. Demanding the two equalities -2l(l+1)+b[l(l+1)+4]+2c l(l+1)+6-6b = b and 2b[l(l+1)-2]+c[l(l+1)-2] l(l+1)+6-6b = c, one obtains the cubic equation 9b3 -15b2 +[6-4l(l+1)]b+4l(l+1) = 0 for the coefficient b, whose solutions are given by Eqs. (28)-(30). The decoupled wave equations are then given by [d2 dr2 + œâ2 - ¬µ2 - l(l+1)+6-6b r2]œÜ = 0, see Eqs. (31)-(33)</subfield>
